description.p:
This invention relates to an isotactic propylene homopolymer (iPP) having:
a) more than 15 and less than 90 regio defects (sum of 2,1-erythro and 2,1-threo insertions, and 3,1- isomerizations) per 10,000 propylene units;
b) a weight average molecular weight (Mw) of 50,000 g/mol or more;
c) a melting peak temperature,Tmp, (as measured by DSC) of greater than 149 °C;
d) mmmm pentads fraction of 0.85 or more;
e) a heat of fusion (ΔHf) of 80 J/g or more; and
f) a melting peak temperature minus crystallization peak temperature (Tmp-Tcp, also referred to as supercooling range) of less than or equal to (0.907 times Tmp) minus 99.64 (or expressed by the formula: Tmp-Tcp < (0.907xTmp) - 99.64), as measured in °C on the homopolymer having 0 wt % nucleating agent.

